UGA_SA_metadata2 <- data.frame(sample_id = UGA_SA_metadata$sample_id, 
                               group = UGA_SA_metadata$condition, 
                               country = UGA_SA_metadata$country)

d2 <- dmDSdata(counts = UGA_SA, samples = UGA_SA_metadata2)

## Subsetting to a vignette runnable size
d2 <- d2[names(d2) %in% gene_id_subset, ]

## Filtering
d2 <- dmFilter(d2, min_samps_gene_expr = 7, min_samps_feature_expr = 3,
               min_gene_expr = 10, min_feature_expr = 10)

## Create the design matrix
design_full2 <- model.matrix(~ group + country, data = samples(d2))
#design_full2

## To make the analysis reproducible
set.seed(123)

## Calculate precision
d2 <- dmPrecision(d2, design = design_full2)
## ! Using a subset of 0.1 genes to estimate common precision !
## ! Using common_precision = 21.2862 as prec_init !
## ! Using 0 as a shrinkage factor !
d2
## An object of class dmDSprecision 
## with 19 genes and 42 samples
## * data accessors: counts(), samples()
##   design()
##   mean_expression(), common_precision(), genewise_precision()
#common_precision(d2)
#head(genewise_precision(d2))

plotPrecision(d2)

## Fit proportions
d2 <- dmFit(d2, design = design_full2, verbose = 1)
## * Fitting the DM model..
##    Using the regression approach.
## Took 0.6139 seconds.
## * Fitting the BB model..
##    Using the regression approach.

## ----DRIMSeq_batch_plotProportions, out.width = "14cm", fig.width = 14-----
## Plot the top significant gene
res2 <- results(d2)
res2 <- res2[order(res2$pvalue, decreasing = FALSE), ]
top_gene_id2 <- res2$gene_id[1]
ggp <- plotProportions(d2, gene_id = top_gene_id2, group_variable = "group")
ggp + facet_wrap(~ country)

# Single p-value per gene
res.g = DRIMSeq::results(d)
# Single p-value per transcript
res.t = DRIMSeq::results(d, level = "feature")
no.na <- function(x) ifelse(is.na(x), 1, x)                            
res.t$pvalue <- no.na(res.t$pvalue)
res.g$pvalue <- no.na(res.g$pvalue)

plotProportions(d, gene_id = top_gene_id2, 
                group_variable = "condition", plot_type = "boxplot1")
